The Hyptidinae, a subtribe of the Lamiaceae family, currently contains 19 genera and around 400 species which are herbs and shrubs distributed mainly in tropical America, from the southern United States and the Caribbean, to Argentina. Some species were introduced in the Old World as weeds and two species occur naturally in tropical Africa. Brazil has the main diversity within the subtribe, with occurrence of species in different vegetations, especially the Atlantic Rain Forest and Cerrado, region that includes the states of Minas Gerais, Bahia, Goi√°s, among others (
 Harley et al., 2004, 
 2012; 
 Pastore et al., 2011; 
 Harley and Pastore, 2012).
